712072f-a.title: Manhattan: 33rd Street (West) - 10th Avenue
712072f-a.text:
W. 33rd Street (diagonally across view from lower richt corner, buildings thereon), west from Tenth Avenue (right foreground ) to the North (Hudson) River. The photographer shows a general view of this West Side area that is prominently sprinkled with vards of the New York Central Railroad. In the background is the North (Hudson) Riwer and the Jersey shoreline.
December 20, 1930.
P.L. Sperr
